Governor Abdulaziz Yari Abubakar of Zamfara State has said he will not leave the APC despite the setback the party faced over the outcome of the recent Supreme Court ruling. Gov. Yari who spoke to newsmen in his home town of Talata Mafara, said since he was one of the founding fathers of the APC, he had no intention of dumping the party as demanded by some of his supporters. “Former Governors of Lagos, Babatunde Fashola; Osun, Rauf Aregbesola; the Governor of Imo, Rochas Okorocha; the current Governor of Ekiti State, Kayode Fayemi, and I toiled hard to build this party. Therefore, I will not abandon the house I helped to build. The struggle has just started,” he said. Grumbling in states as govs anoint successors Breaking: I'll remain in APC to fight injustice, support Buhari's 're election -Marafa Marafa pledges to remain in APC, work for Buhari Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin